 Two men lost their lives in a collision at about 06:00 on the corner of Mandela Drive and Samora Machel Street. One of the vehicles involved in the collision on Samora Machel and Mandela Drive. In an unrelated incident shortly after 11:00, three people died near the Kranspoort Pass on the N11 in a head-on collision between a Toyota Avanza and a Ford Figo. According to the Mpumalanga Community Safety and Liaison Department four of the Avanza passengers were seriously injured and two people who were travelling in the Figo also had to be transported to the hospital. The incident caused a 2 hour delay on the busy road. The accident scene in Kranspoort.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za